Key Match Events: Haris Rauf scored 35 runs off 23 balls, achieving a strike rate of 152.17.
David Willey took 3 wickets for 56 runs and was named Man of the Match.
England won by 93 runs, sealing qualification for the 2025 Champions Trophy.
Post-Match Reflections: Jos Buttler expressed disappointment but praised David Willey's performance and acknowledged the need for changes in the team.
Babar Azam admitted that Pakistan conceded too many runs and needs to improve their spinners' performance.
Miscellaneous Highlights: England's Ben Stokes scored 84 runs, while Pakistan's Haris Rauf scored 35 runs.
Pakistan was bowled out for 244, needing 94 runs to win in 42 overs.
